doc.after: Hand starting of aircraft piston engines by swinging the propeller is the oldest and simplest method the absence of any onboard starting system giving an appreciable weight saving Positioning of the propeller relative to the crankshaft is arranged such that the engine pistons pass through top dead centre during the swinging stroke
